                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.00/2510: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador to the Polish Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-27T23:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 27, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Polish Series No. 30. Your November 26, 2 p.m., Polish Series No. 44. As the
                    President’s statement of October 25 was made independently, we do not now wish
                    to associate ourselves in a joint undertaking of any kind protesting violence
                    against civilians in occupied countries. We do, of course, appreciate the
                    intention of the allied Governments established in London to base their proposed
                    joint declaration on the President’s statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
